chunks.texto_chunk: --- PÁGINA 1 --- Frau Elisabeth Aebersold Herzogenacker 53 B 3654 Gunten, Switzerland. Gunten, 7th [[February]] 1986. **Sr. Presidente Belisario Betancur** **Bogotá. ** Dear Mr. President, I am deeply alarmed at the reports of "disappearance" of **Pablo Caicedo Siachoque** and **Marco Fidel Castro,** who have been detained on 19 November 1985 after leaving the Cali UP offices by members of the security forces.

Their detentions **have not been acknowledged** by the authorities. We received informations, that both are being held at the Tolemaida military base in Melgar. **In the name of the Declaration of the Human Rights of the UNO, which was ratified by your government,** I beg you to clarify their whereabouts and to order, that they are being humanely treated. I do appeal to you most urgently, dear Mr. President, that these prisoners are promptly brought before a court and charged with a recognizable criminal offence **or released without delay!** Yours sincerely and respectfully *[firma manuscrita]* **Frau Elisabeth Aebersold** Copies to: General Miguel Vega Uribe Comité Permanente por la Defensa de los Derechos Humanos Ambassade de Colombie, Bern.
